<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 8:44AM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A cluster of strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
Scotland, Anson, south central Montgomery, Richmond, southeastern
Stanly and southwestern Hoke Counties through 945 AM EDT...
At 843 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Chesterfield, or 13 miles west of Cheraw, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Rockingham, Wadesboro, Hamlet, Maxton, Ansonville,
Hoffman, Polkton, Ellerbe and Dobbins Heights.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
